Package: MixedPsy
Version: 1.0.0
Title: Statistical Tools for the Analysis of Psychophysical Data
Authors@R: c(
    person("Alessandro", "Moscatelli", email = "moskante@gmail.com", role = c("aut","cre")),
    person("Priscilla", "Balestrucci", email = "priscilla.balestrucci@gmail.com", role = "aut"))
Maintainer: Alessandro Moscatelli <moskante@gmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 3.1.0)
Description: Tools for the analysis of psychophysical data in R. This package allows to estimate the Point of Subjective Equivalence (PSE) and the Just Noticeable Difference (JND), either from a psychometric function or from a Generalized Linear Mixed Model. Additionally, the package allows plotting the fitted models and the response data, simulating psychometric functions of different shapes, and simulating data sets.
Imports:
  beepr,
  boot,
  brglm,
  lme4,
  Matrix,
  mnormt
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat
